      "message": "This and the equivalent in HandleExceptionWithBroker() should probably record something via Metrics::ExceptionCaptureResult(). I think we do want a result for every Metrics::ExceptionEncountered(). That does appear to be how we do things on macOS and Windows.\n\nFeel free to add something to the Metrics::CaptureResult enum to encompass these failures. Because this is used for an UMA metric, the rules are (1) don’t change existing values, and (2) when this rolls into Chrome, update tools/metrics/histograms/histograms.xml too. (Actually, you can update Chrome before this rolls into it if you’re not planning a Crashpad roll soon and are afraid of losing track.)",
